article.description: Georgie Pacheco-Ortiz had 12 points as Liberty romped past South Carolina State 65-39 on Tuesday night.
article.headline: Pacheco-Ortiz leads Liberty past SC State 65-39
article.linkText: Pacheco-Ortiz leads Liberty past SC State 65-39
article.story: LYNCHBURG, Va. -- Georgie Pacheco-Ortiz had 12 points as Liberty romped past South Carolina State 65-39 on Tuesday night. Caleb Homesley had 10 points and six rebounds for Liberty (3-0). Darius McGhee added six rebounds. Scottie James had 12 rebounds for the hosts. Jahmari Etienne had 14 points for the Bulldogs (1-2). Damni Applewhite added nine rebounds. Liberty takes on East Carolina on the road on Saturday. South Carolina State faces Wilberforce at home on Monday. --- For more AP college basketball coverage: https://apnews.com/Collegebasketball and http://twitter.com/AP-Top25 --- This was generated by Automated Insights, http://www.automatedinsights.com/ap, using data from STATS LLC, https://www.stats.com
